    • Method Detail

      • add

        boolean add(IntervalIF<T> interval)
        Append the passed interval object to this range set.
        The passed interval have to be disjoint and non adjacent to the current range set.
        Only defined interval objects will be added
        Parameters:
        interval - - the interval object to append
        Returns:
        true (as specified by Collection.add(E))

      • mergeAdd

        boolean mergeAdd(IntervalIF<T> interval)
        Appends the passed interval to this 'RangeIF' object. If the passed interval intersects the last interval of this range set or is adjacent to it, the last interval and the passed one would be merged to a new last interval of this range set
        Parameters:
        interval - - the interval object to append
        Returns:
        true if adding of the passed interval was successful, false otherwise
